#Text=The Philadelphia 76ers ( 3 - 31 ) upset the Sacramento Kings ( 12 - 20 ) 111 - 105 on Wednesday night .
#Text=In a battle of two bad teams , poor execution was on display .
#Text=Most notably , the shooting was bad all - around .
#Text=Both teams shot shy of 62 percent from the free - throw line and both teams shot right around 30 percent from long distance .
#Text=The Sixers are the most turnover prone team in the NBA , but they dominated that battle here , committing 13 to the Kings 22 .
#Text=The pace was incredible in this game as well , as there were a combined 168 shots and 75 combined free - throws .
#Text=The Sixers are a revived team as of late and it directly correlates with the addition of Ish Smith .
#Text=They have been competitive in three - straight games and committing far less turnovers .
#Text=That 's what a veteran point guard will bring to a team and it 's clear they made a good move here after numerous poor decisions in the past .
#Text=He was Philly 's best player tonight , as he tallied 18 points , nine assists , three rebounds , two steals and two blocks in the win .
#Text=Nerlens Noel also had a good game , as he collected 20 points , nine rebounds and four steals .
#Text=Jahlil Okafor also made his return here from a knee injury and put in a double - double off the bench in just 20 minutes of play .
#Text=In addition , Jerami Grant was extremely active in this game , as he recorded a double - double and pitched in seven combined blocks and steals in the game .
#Text=Philadelphia has a good chance to continue their recent good stretch against the Los Angeles Lakers on Friday .
#Text=This sort of game is a microcosm of the Kings season .
#Text=The talent discrepancy on paper in this game was truly unfair , yet this game was close throughout and they trailed for the entirety of the second half .
#Text=The sloppy play really killed this team , as they shot well but committed 22 turnovers .
#Text=DeMarcus Cousins was Sacramento 's best player , as he totaled 21 points , 12 rebounds and three blocks in the loss .
#Text=Rajon Rondo also had a good game despite committing seven turnovers , as he amassed eight points , 14 assists and five rebounds .
#Text=Marco Belinelli also had an impressive game off the bench , scoring a season - high 28 points .
#Text=There were many instances throughout the game where the fans were booing their home team and that 's a sad indication of where this franchise is right now .
#Text=They 'll host the Phoenix Suns in their next game on Saturday in a battle of disgruntled teams .
